cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.MA. 

The paper deals with information theory and communication systems, specifically the cut-off rate of a fading channel. Therefore, cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of side information, which falls under cs.SI (Signal Processing and Information Theory) and cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture). Finally, the paper uses mathematical techniques to derive upper bounds, which could fall under cs.MA (Mathematical Software) or cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
